When formula_15 this is the only intersecting family of this size. However, when formula_2, there is a more general construction. Each set can be matched up to its complement, the only set from which it is disjoint. Then, choose one set from each of these complementary pairs. For instance, for the same parameters above, this more general construction can be used to form the family

where every two sets intersect despite no element belonging to all three sets. In this example, all of the sets have been complemented from the ones in the first example, but it is also possible to complement only some of the sets.

